<span id="freeTextContainer668278387817609863">Overall, this one was a good reading experience except for when Leo started to talk about his relationship with his lovers. In different format of story telling what he was revealing probably more acceptable, but in this book, the intended reader supposed to be his Son. I could not believe peoples in Leo&apos;s life time revealing so much about their intimate relationship to their son, however close the father and son bond was. </span>
