        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer607068379" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3770826978456362134">Wow, what a story! I would consider this book an epic, and I&apos;m actually disappointed that I&apos;ve finished it and can now no longer continue on these travels. The author does a really great job telling this story from Hasan/Leo&apos;s perspective, and even the cheesy parts just come off as nostalgic and meaningful. The conclusion of the book wasn&apos;t quite as comprehensive as I&apos;d expected it to be, but I&apos;m actually fine with it regardless. This is, after all, meant to read like a memoir written in the 16t</span>
  <span id="freeText3770826978456362134" style="display:none">Wow, what a story! I would consider this book an epic, and I'm actually disappointed that I've finished it and can now no longer continue on these travels. The author does a really great job telling this story from Hasan/Leo's perspective, and even the cheesy parts just come off as nostalgic and meaningful. The conclusion of the book wasn't quite as comprehensive as I'd expected it to be, but I'm actually fine with it regardless. This is, after all, meant to read like a memoir written in the 16th century, and not necessarily like a more modern work of literature. As such, I have no real complaints about the book. I feel that this one will stick with me for a while.</span>
