<span id="freeTextContainer758373075357376801">I am a fan of historical novels. Let that be clear. But I have read better ones than this one. I&apos;d say the story is too much of a factual acccount. Little is revealed about how the characters think or feel, or what position they take in certain conflicts or situations. <br/>Although one cannot deny that as lives go, the life that the main character led is quite unbelievable in the least, especially since it is not an imaginary story but based on facts.<br/>Maybe I would have appreciated the story more, ha</span>
  <span id="freeText758373075357376801" style="display:none">I am a fan of historical novels. Let that be clear. But I have read better ones than this one. I'd say the story is too much of a factual acccount. Little is revealed about how the characters think or feel, or what position they take in certain conflicts or situations. <br />Although one cannot deny that as lives go, the life that the main character led is quite unbelievable in the least, especially since it is not an imaginary story but based on facts.<br />Maybe I would have appreciated the story more, had I known more about the main character and his role in history as such, but I did not feel inclined to read up on him because I felt little or no particular sympathy for him, because so little is said about his emotional life.<br />Not one that I would recommend.</span>
